Note: Hispanics are those who say they are Hispanic. Those who do not self-identify as
Hispanic say they are not Hispanic or Latino but say they have Hispanic ancestry or heritage.
Second generation refers to those born in the 50 states or District of Columbia to at least
one immigrant parent. Third generation refers to those born in the 50 states or D. C. to
parents and grandparents who are U.S born. Fourth or higher generation refers to those
born in the 50 states or D.C. with parents, grandparents, great grandparents, or jeven more
distant relatives, who are born in the 50 states or D. C.
Source: Pew Research Center 2015 National Survey of Latinos (Oct. 21-Nov. 30, 2015) and
